OL,3,CCharities and councils warn of
OL,4,Cchildren's social care 'breaking point'
OL,6,FCouncils and charities have joined
OL,7,Fforces to call on the Government to
OL,8,Fstabilise a children's social care
OL,9,Fsystem at "breaking point", and
OL,10,Fbolster protections in "progressively
OL,11,Fchallenging circumstances".
OL,13,FOrganisations providing support to
OL,14,Fchildren said it is vital that
OL,15,Fadditional funding is included in the
OL,16,Fforthcoming spending review to ensure
OL,17,Fchildren and young people are shielded
OL,18,Ffrom harm at a time of rising demand
OL,19,Fand costs.
