OL,3,CCharities and councils warn of
OL,4,Cchildren's social care 'breaking point'
OL,6,FAs demand for support has remained
OL,7,Fstubbornly high in recent years, costs
OL,8,Fhave increased sharply, leading to
OL,9,Freductions in spending on prevention
OL,10,Fservices in many areas.
OL,12,FChildren's social care budgets in 2024/
OL,13,F25 overall increased by 11% on the
OL,14,Fprevious year to #14.2 billion, driven
OL,15,Fby rising costs of residential
OL,16,Fplacements, most of which are provided
OL,17,Fby the private sector, and growing
OL,18,Fneed for specialist support for
OL,19,Fchildren with complex needs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
