OL,3,CCharities and councils warn of
OL,4,Cchildren's social care 'breaking point'
OL,6,FThe coalition's research found
OL,7,Fspending by councils on early
OL,8,Fintervention services has dropped by
OL,9,Fmore than #2 billion, or 42%, since
OL,10,F2010/11, at a time when spending on
OL,11,Fresidential care for children has
OL,12,Frisen to a record high.
OL,14,F"With around 1,700 children being
OL,15,Freferred to social care every day, and
OL,16,Fwith increasingly complex needs, it's
OL,17,Fnever been more important that
OL,18,Fservices can match this growing demand
OL,19,Fand reach families early on before
OL,20,Fthey hit crisis point," the coalition
OL,21,Fadded.
